function.name: countries_for_geodb_cities
function.description: This is the subfunction for tool "geodb_cities", you can use this tool.The description of this function is: "Find countries, filtering by optional criteria. If no criteria are set, you will get back all known countries."

function.name: time_zone_for_geodb_cities
function.description: This is the subfunction for tool "geodb_cities", you can use this tool.The description of this function is: "Get the time-zone current time in ISO-6801 format: HHmmss.SSSZ"

function.name: time_zones_for_geodb_cities
function.description: This is the subfunction for tool "geodb_cities", you can use this tool.The description of this function is: "Get all known time-zones."

function.name: currencies_for_geodb_cities
function.description: This is the subfunction for tool "geodb_cities", you can use this tool.The description of this function is: "Get currencies, filtering by optional criteria. If no criteria are set, you will get back all known currencies."

function.name: city_details_for_geodb_cities
function.description: This is the subfunction for tool "geodb_cities", you can use this tool.The description of this function is: "Get the details for a specific city, including location coordinates, population, and elevation above sea-level (if available)."

cityid.description: The city id (either native id or wikiDataId)

function.name: admin_divisions_near_location_for_geodb_cities
function.description: This is the subfunction for tool "geodb_cities", you can use this tool.The description of this function is: "Get administrative divisions near the given location, filtering by optional criteria."

locationid.description: Only divisions near this location. Latitude/longitude in ISO-6709 format: ±DD.DDDD±DDD.DDDD

radius.description: The location radius within which to find divisions

excludedcountryids.description: Only divisions NOT in these countries (comma-delimited country codes or WikiData ids)

offset.description: The zero-ary offset into the results

limit.description: The maximum number of results to retrieve

nameprefixdefaultlangresults.description: When name-prefix matching, whether or not to match on names in the default language if a non-default language is requested

countryids.description: Only divisions in these countries (comma-delimited country codes or WikiData ids)

minpopulation.description: Only divisions having at least this population

includedeleted.description: Whether to include any divisions marked deleted: ALL | SINCE_YESTERDAY | SINCE_LAST_WEEK | NONE

maxpopulation.description: Only divisions having no more than this population

distanceunit.description: The unit of distance to use: MI | KM

sort.description: How to sort the results. Format: ±SORT_FIELD,±SORT_FIELD where SORT_FIELD = countryCode | elevation | name | population

nameprefix.description: Only divisions whose names start with this prefix. If languageCode is set, the prefix will be matched on the name as it appears in that language.

function.name: admin_divisions_near_division_for_geodb_cities
function.description: This is the subfunction for tool "geodb_cities", you can use this tool.The description of this function is: "Get divisions near the given administrative division, filtering by optional criteria."

radius.description: The location radius within which to find divisions

minpopulation.description: Only divisions having at least this population

nameprefixdefaultlangresults.description: When name-prefix matching, whether or not to match on names in the default language if a non-default language is requested

maxpopulation.description: Only divisions having no more than this population

distanceunit.description: The unit of distance to use: MI | KM

offset.description: The zero-ary offset into the results

excludedcountryids.description: Only divisions NOT in these countries (comma-delimited country codes or WikiData ids)

limit.description: The maximum number of results to retrieve

countryids.description: Only divisions in these countries (comma-delimited country codes or WikiData ids)

nameprefix.description: Only divisions whose names start with this prefix. If languageCode is set, the prefix will be matched on the name as it appears in that language.

sort.description: How to sort the results. Format: ±SORT_FIELD,±SORT_FIELD where SORT_FIELD = countryCode | elevation | name | population

includedeleted.description: Whether to include any divisions marked deleted: ALL | SINCE_YESTERDAY | SINCE_LAST_WEEK | NONE

function.name: time_zone_date_time_for_geodb_cities
function.description: This is the subfunction for tool "geodb_cities", you can use this tool.The description of this function is: "Get the timezone current date-time in ISO-6801 format: yyyyMMdd'T'HHmmssZ"

function.name: Finish
function.description: If you believe that you have obtained a result that can answer the task, please call this function to provide the final answer. Alternatively, if you recognize that you are unable to proceed with the task in the current state, call this function to restart. Remember: you must ALWAYS call this function at the end of your attempt, and the only part that will be shown to the user is the final answer, so it should contain sufficient information.
